Jeanette Chabalala, News24 (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; Crystal meth with an estimated street value of R15m was recovered at Durban Container Terminal on Monday, KwaZulu-Natal police said. &nbsp;Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo said an intelligence operation was conducted by Hawks, SA Revenue Service and Durban Harbour ORS officers at the terminal.The drugs, weighing 60kg, were hidden in cargo bags hidden among food boxes.No arrests have yet been made.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.